STEPS FOLLOWED TO LAUNCH MY FIRST EC2 AMAZON LINUX.

Name	my-first-ec2
Amazon Machine Image (AMI)	Amazon Linux 2023 (Free Tier eligible) ✅
Instance Type	t2.micro (Free Tier eligible) ✅
Key Pair	Create new key pair → Name it mykey → Download mykey.pem
Network Settings	✅ Allow SSH (port 22) — choose My IP for security
Storage	Leave as default (8 GB is fine)
Tags	Optional — leave blank
Advanced Settings	Ignore for now

## Steps Followed
- Launched Amazon Linux EC2 (Free Tier)
- Configured SSH key pair: mykey.pem
- Allowed access only from my IP
- Connected to EC2 via SSH

## What I Did
- Created and launched EC2 (Amazon Linux 2023, t2.micro)
- Created SSH key and used it to connect securely
- Verified connection using Git Bash + SSH

## Commands used in Git Bash for ec2 creation
cd ~/Downloads               # Go to Downloads folder
ls                           # List files there
chmod 400 mykey.pem          # Secure your AWS key
ssh -i "mykey.pem" ec2-user@ec2-3-...amazonaws.com   # Login to EC2
# Git basics
git init                     # Start repo
git add .                    # Stage all files
git commit -m "Message"      # Commit changes
git push origin main         # Push to GitHub
